{
  "texts": [
    "You are a Labour voter in the United Kingdom, from Guildford, which was a competitive district in 2019 under the first-past-the-post system.",
    "During the campaign, there was only one public opinion poll to inform your vote choice should you want to vote tactically.",
    "Moreover, the sample size of the poll was small (500 respondents) and the time frame of the poll relatively uncertain, conducted between the 21st and 26th of November, and potentially outdated relative to the election day of the 12th of December.",
    "The poll showed a very tight race between the Liberal Democrats and the Conservatives, giving the former a 1% lead.",
    "If you trust this result, you have good reasons to vote tactically for the LibDem to avoid the worst outcome by your light, a Conservative victory."
  ]
}